<kml>

<concept name=Be-Open>
<superconcept name=Be-Accessible>

<hr>
<h3>Component Semantics:</h3>
<component tag=Be-Open>
  <definition>an object is opened</definition>
  <requiredslot name=object>
    <restriction>exactly 1 Portal-Covering</restriction>
    <restriction>the Portal-Covering <slot>is-part-of</slot> a <conceptref name=Tangible-Entity></restriction>    
  </requiredslot>
  <wnsynsets>open#1, open#5, opened#1
  </wnsynsets>
  <wnsynsets>unfastened#2
  </wnsynsets>
</component>

<musing>
The <conceptref name=Open> action puts an <slot>object</slot> into 
the Be-Open state while at the same time taking the object out of
the <conceptref name=Be-Closed> state. The action <conceptref name=Close> 
does the exact opposite.
</musing>

</kml>


